nbsCmmcMib.name: nbsCmmcMib
nbsCmmcMib.contactinfo: For technical support, please contact your service channel
nbsCmmcMib.description: MIB for representing NBS CMMC information

nbsCmmcObjects.name: nbsCmmcObjects
nbsCmmcObjects.description: all MIB objects in nbsCmmc MIB.

nbsCmmcSysFwDescr.name: nbsCmmcSysFwDescr
nbsCmmcSysFwDescr.description: The description of the System Control Firmware.

nbsCmmcSysFwVers.name: nbsCmmcSysFwVers
nbsCmmcSysFwVers.description: The System Control Firmware version in the form Vmajor.minor.

nbsCmmcSysRestart.name: nbsCmmcSysRestart
nbsCmmcSysRestart.description: This object is used to reset the system. Writing a coldRestart(2), causes the SNMP Agent CPU to be hardware reset, similar to a power-on cycle. Writing a warmRestart(3), causes only a restart of the System Control CPU operative software. Writing a upgrRestart(4), causes a total restart of the system software, but attempts to leave the hardware alone.

nbsCmmcSysNumRestarts.name: nbsCmmcSysNumRestarts
nbsCmmcSysNumRestarts.description: Number of warmRestarts executed by the system, since the last coldRestart or power-on cycle. A warmRestart may be initiated by: - writing a warmRestart value in nbsCmmcSysRestart - a warmRestart command from the Command Line. - the SNMP Agent Firmware due to certain conditions.

nbsCmmcSysErrUptime.name: nbsCmmcSysErrUptime
nbsCmmcSysErrUptime.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) since the last cold reset/power cycle when a fatal error occurred. This variable shows the system uptime from the last cold reset/power on cycle, unless a fatal error oc- curred.

nbsCmmcSysSetNvramDefaults.name: nbsCmmcSysSetNvramDefaults
nbsCmmcSysSetNvramDefaults.description: Writing the value setDefaults to this objects will re- store the defaults in the NVRAM data base. These values will take effect after a system reset. For the Linux-based NM family, after restoring defaults, take care not to commit running changes with the nbsCmmcSysWriteConfig object. Doing so would undo the defaults, overwriting them with the running configuration.

nbsCmmcSysSelftestLevel.name: nbsCmmcSysSelftestLevel
nbsCmmcSysSelftestLevel.description: NVRAM based level of the system selftest. The values are : ststNone - meaning that no selftest will be executed upon boot-up ststShort- meaning that a short selftest, of approx 10-20 seconds will be executed upon boot- up ststLong - meaning that a long/extensive self-test will be executed upon boot-up ststDiagnostics - meaning that upon boot-up the di- agnostics mode is entered. In this mode it is possible to interactively select the test or the group of tests that will be executed. This value may not be set through a SNMP SET command. This object is deprecated.

nbsCmmcSysCurrentTime.name: nbsCmmcSysCurrentTime
nbsCmmcSysCurrentTime.description: The current time, expressed as the number of seconds since 00:00 (midnight) 1 January 1900 GMT. Obtained via Time Protocol (RFC 868) or set by user. Not supported value: 0

nbsCmmcSysCurrentDateTime.name: nbsCmmcSysCurrentDateTime
nbsCmmcSysCurrentDateTime.description: The current time, derived from nbsCmmcSysCurrentTime, adjusted to Agent's local time (nbsCmmcSysTimeZone), expressed in the format 'www mm dd hh:mm:ss yyyy'. If nbsCmmcSysCurrentTime is 0, this value should be 'unknown'.

nbsCmmcSysNvramTable.name: nbsCmmcSysNvramTable
nbsCmmcSysNvramTable.description: Copy of Non-Volatile RAM kept in Agent, including all settings, configurations, and names for all cards managed by this Agent.

nbsCmmcSysNvramBlock.name: nbsCmmcSysNvramBlock
nbsCmmcSysNvramBlock.description: Bytes contained in this block of NVRAM.

nbsCmmcSysWriteConfig.name: nbsCmmcSysWriteConfig
nbsCmmcSysWriteConfig.description: This object is used to write the configuration file. If this returns supported, the SNMP Agent requires you to specifically write the configuration file. Any changes that are not written out will be lost on next reboot. Setting copyTempFile(4) will copy the file uploaded via nbsCmmcSysNvramTable into the non-volatile startup area.

nbsCmmcSysUpgrade.name: nbsCmmcSysUpgrade
nbsCmmcSysUpgrade.description: This object allows user to initiate a transfer of firmware from the NM file system to the cards in selected slots. Before using, user should ensure the proper files have been loaded (TFTP'd) onto the NM. This object has read-write access so it will be more universally compilable, but is intended only for writing. For reading, the contents are undefined. The string should contain a comma-separated list of slots to be reprogrammed, in the format chassis.slot, or chassis.* to load all cards. While the NM is reprogramming the line card, SNMP communication may be temporarily suspended.

nbsCmmcSysLoginIdleTimeout.name: nbsCmmcSysLoginIdleTimeout
nbsCmmcSysLoginIdleTimeout.description: This object is used to control the idle logout timer. This timer is in minutes. If a user logged into the CLI has not typed anything for this number of minutes, the session is automatically closed. Zero means no automatic timeout.

nbsCmmcSysDiscoveryAdmin.name: nbsCmmcSysDiscoveryAdmin
nbsCmmcSysDiscoveryAdmin.description: The Discovery protocol allows Linux NM cards to find each other on a single layer 2 network segment. By default it is enabled.

nbsCmmcSysDiscoveryOper.name: nbsCmmcSysDiscoveryOper
nbsCmmcSysDiscoveryOper.description: The current operational status of the Discovery protocol.

nbsCmmcSysDiscoveryHostTable.name: nbsCmmcSysDiscoveryHostTable
nbsCmmcSysDiscoveryHostTable.description: Table that contains host information found using the L2 Discovery protocol

nbsCmmcSysDiscoveryHostEntry.name: nbsCmmcSysDiscoveryHostEntry
nbsCmmcSysDiscoveryHostEntry.description: Represents a single host found using the L2 Discovery protocol

nbsCmmcSysDiscoveryHostDistance.name: nbsCmmcSysDiscoveryHostDistance
nbsCmmcSysDiscoveryHostDistance.description: How many hops from me is this host?

nbsCmmcSysDiscoveryHostAddressType.name: nbsCmmcSysDiscoveryHostAddressType
nbsCmmcSysDiscoveryHostAddressType.description: IP address type, select IPv4 or IPv6

nbsCmmcSysDiscoveryHostAddress.name: nbsCmmcSysDiscoveryHostAddress
nbsCmmcSysDiscoveryHostAddress.description: IPv4 or IPv6 IP address of discovered host, this replaces nbsCmmcSysDiscoveryHostIPAddress

nbsCmmcSysDiscoveryHostSourceIfIndex.name: nbsCmmcSysDiscoveryHostSourceIfIndex
nbsCmmcSysDiscoveryHostSourceIfIndex.description: Interface index that the discovered host was found by. 0 for the local host.

nbsCmmcSysLastSetFailure.name: nbsCmmcSysLastSetFailure
nbsCmmcSysLastSetFailure.description: If the last SNMP SET was rejected, for example with SNMP Error: BadValue (SNMP Error 3), this object should explain why the SET failed. This string may be empty (size 0) if no explanation is available. If there have been no SET requests since boot-up, this string should be empty (size 0). In addition to this object, SET errors may also be found in the nbsCmmcSysRunningLogMessageTable.

nbsCmmcSysTimeProtocol.name: nbsCmmcSysTimeProtocol
nbsCmmcSysTimeProtocol.description: Time Protocol (RFC 868) allows the managed device to synchronize its clock with a Time Server. When read, the agent will report notSupported(1) if this object is not supported. When set to enabled(3), it will cause the agent to contact the nbsCmmcSysTimeServer (if valid) via rdate to obtain the current time. disabled(2) is a deprecated, legacy value. Setting this value will cause a SET error.

nbsCmmcSysTimeServer.name: nbsCmmcSysTimeServer
nbsCmmcSysTimeServer.description: The IP Address of the Time Server.

nbsCmmcSysTimeServAddressType.name: nbsCmmcSysTimeServAddressType
nbsCmmcSysTimeServAddressType.description: The Address Type of the Time Server.

nbsCmmcSysTimeServAddress.name: nbsCmmcSysTimeServAddress
nbsCmmcSysTimeServAddress.description: The IPv4 or IPv6 Address of the Time Server. This entry replaces nbsCmmcSysTimeServer

nbsCmmcSysFirmwareTable.name: nbsCmmcSysFirmwareTable
nbsCmmcSysFirmwareTable.description: Table that lists firmware images loaded on NM.

nbsCmmcSysFirmwareFilename.name: nbsCmmcSysFirmwareFilename
nbsCmmcSysFirmwareFilename.description: The filename of the firmware package. If it is in the format scheme://host/path, it refers to nbsCmmcSysFirmwareURL.

nbsCmmcSysFirmwareSize.name: nbsCmmcSysFirmwareSize
nbsCmmcSysFirmwareSize.description: The size (in bytes) of the firmware package file

nbsCmmcSysFirmwareMTime.name: nbsCmmcSysFirmwareMTime
nbsCmmcSysFirmwareMTime.description: The last modified time of the firmware package file itself.

nbsCmmcSysFirmwareVersion.name: nbsCmmcSysFirmwareVersion
nbsCmmcSysFirmwareVersion.description: The version of the firmware package

nbsCmmcSysFirmwareDate.name: nbsCmmcSysFirmwareDate
nbsCmmcSysFirmwareDate.description: The date of release of the firmware package in RFC 2822 format

nbsCmmcSysFirmwareType.name: nbsCmmcSysFirmwareType
nbsCmmcSysFirmwareType.description: What kind of entity this package is for. Valid rev files have type chassis(2), slot(3), or port(4). invalid(1) indicates this entry is not a valid rev file. deleted(5) indicates this entry refers to a file that was deleted and is no longer in the management card storage area. This entry may be re-enabled if the identical file is again put on the management card. This way, indexes do not move around if files are deleted and subsequently restored. However, deleted slots may be reused by the system for new files at the system's descretion. Setting deleted(5) will delete this file permanently from the management card storage area. No values other than deleted(5) can be set.

nbsCmmcSysFirmwareIDCs.name: nbsCmmcSysFirmwareIDCs
nbsCmmcSysFirmwareIDCs.description: A comma separated list of module versions supported by this firmware package

nbsCmmcSysFirmwareCksum.name: nbsCmmcSysFirmwareCksum
nbsCmmcSysFirmwareCksum.description: The checksum of the metadata. Used to uniquely identify this package file. Invalid package files have a zero Cksum. Not supported value: 0

nbsCmmcSysFirmwareMd5.name: nbsCmmcSysFirmwareMd5
nbsCmmcSysFirmwareMd5.description: The MD5 checksum of this firmware image. Used to verify the integrity of this package file.

nbsCmmcSysTimeZone.name: nbsCmmcSysTimeZone
nbsCmmcSysTimeZone.description: User-configurable TimeZone or offset from GMT. Should be used to indicate the time local to the managed device. If the system supports nbsCmmcSysTimeZoneTableSize and it is non-zero, this object is the nbsCmmcSysTimeZoneIndex of nbsCmmcSysTimeZoneTable, which enumerates all the time zones that this system supports.

nbsCmmcSysSnmpV1.name: nbsCmmcSysSnmpV1
nbsCmmcSysSnmpV1.description: This object enables or disables SNMPv1 protocol handling.

nbsCmmcSysSnmpV2c.name: nbsCmmcSysSnmpV2c
nbsCmmcSysSnmpV2c.description: This object enables or disables SNMPv2c protocol handling.

nbsCmmcSysSnmpV3.name: nbsCmmcSysSnmpV3
nbsCmmcSysSnmpV3.description: This object enables or disables SNMPv3 protocol handling.

nbsCmmcSysStpAdmin.name: nbsCmmcSysStpAdmin
nbsCmmcSysStpAdmin.description: This object enables or disables STP protocol handling.

nbsCmmcSysStpOper.name: nbsCmmcSysStpOper
nbsCmmcSysStpOper.description: The current operational status of the STP protocol.

nbsCmmcSysLockTypes.name: nbsCmmcSysLockTypes
nbsCmmcSysLockTypes.description: If enabled, forces the system only to allow writes to slots/ports that are detected as the same type as the configured type. Use nbsCmmcSlotClearType to clear the configured type. When this object is enabled(3) and a module is inserted that is incompatible with the configured type, Agent should issue the notification nbsCmmcTrapSlotModuleLocked instead of nbsCmmcTrapSlotModuleIn. The notfication nbsCmmcTrapSlotModuleIn should be issued once the lock has been cleared (see nbsCmmcSlotClearType).

nbsCmmcSysSerialTerminalType.name: nbsCmmcSysSerialTerminalType
nbsCmmcSysSerialTerminalType.description: Name of terminal to use for the serial port, e.g. vt100, xterm, ansi.

nbsCmmcSysCrossConnect.name: nbsCmmcSysCrossConnect
nbsCmmcSysCrossConnect.description: For systems which have chassis/slots supporting cross-connect functionality, this object is used to reflect the operating state and clear the entire cross-connect map, including any independent maps of subordinate chassis and slots. If there are currently no cross-connect chassis or slots in this system, the Agent must report notSupported(1). If the cross-connect mappings can not be cleared via this object, and/or can only be cleared via the Chassis, Slot, or PortCrossConnect, the Agent must also report notSupported(1). Additionally, if this object reports notSupported(1), any SNMP SET to this object should return SNMP Error 3 (bad value). If this object reports operating(2), SNMP Managers are allowed to set this object to clearing (3), which instructs the Agent to erase the cross-connect maps of all subordinate chassis and slots, so no circuits exist in the system.

nbsCmmcSysCountersState.name: nbsCmmcSysCountersState
nbsCmmcSysCountersState.description: This object is used to reset all counters in this device. If agent does not have this feature, this object should be notSupported(1). In order to reset all counters to zero, set this object to clearing(3). If this feature is supported, the Agent may return the status clearing (3) during the interval in which it is resetting the counters, but otherwise should return the status counting(2).

nbsCmmcSysSerialBaudRateAdmin.name: nbsCmmcSysSerialBaudRateAdmin
nbsCmmcSysSerialBaudRateAdmin.description: The Serial Console Baud Rate when not in SLIP Mode. Setting this object will change the serial console baud rate in the BootROM configuration. It will not take effect until cold or upgrade restart. Setting this object has no effect on startup-config or the running configuration.

nbsCmmcSysSerialBaudRateOper.name: nbsCmmcSysSerialBaudRateOper
nbsCmmcSysSerialBaudRateOper.description: The current operational Serial Console Baud Rate when not in SLIP Mode.

nbsCmmcSysProtoTableSize.name: nbsCmmcSysProtoTableSize
nbsCmmcSysProtoTableSize.description: The number of entries in nbsCmmcSysProtoTable.

nbsCmmcSysProtoTable.name: nbsCmmcSysProtoTable
nbsCmmcSysProtoTable.description: A table to report supportable data transmission protocols.

nbsCmmcSysProtoEntry.name: nbsCmmcSysProtoEntry
nbsCmmcSysProtoEntry.description: Describes a particular protocol or line rate.

nbsCmmcSysProtoFamily.name: nbsCmmcSysProtoFamily
nbsCmmcSysProtoFamily.description: Family of this protocol. The following family names must be used exactly for machine-readability: SONET T-Carrier E-Carrier Ethernet FibreChannel DigitalVideo Other family names may be added as necessary.

nbsCmmcSysProtoRate.name: nbsCmmcSysProtoRate
nbsCmmcSysProtoRate.description: Speeds or rates associated with this protocol.

nbsCmmcSysTimeZoneTableSize.name: nbsCmmcSysTimeZoneTableSize
nbsCmmcSysTimeZoneTableSize.description: The number of entries in nbsCmmcSysTimeZoneTable.

nbsCmmcSysTimeZoneTable.name: nbsCmmcSysTimeZoneTable
nbsCmmcSysTimeZoneTable.description: A table to report supportable timezones.

nbsCmmcSysTimeZoneIndex.name: nbsCmmcSysTimeZoneIndex
nbsCmmcSysTimeZoneIndex.description: TimeZone index corresponding to a nbsCmmcSysTimeZone setting. The first entry is reserved for 'notSupported'. The next 25 entries are reserved for GMT-12 (gmtMinus1200) through GMT+12 (gmtPlus1200) for compatibility with the older nbsCmmcSysTimeZone enumeration. Entries 27 and up are specific to the system.

nbsCmmcSysLoaderTableSize.name: nbsCmmcSysLoaderTableSize
nbsCmmcSysLoaderTableSize.description: The maximum number of concurrent loader sessions.

nbsCmmcSysLoaderTable.name: nbsCmmcSysLoaderTable
nbsCmmcSysLoaderTable.description: A table to manage multiple loader (transfer from NM to blade or line card) sessions.

nbsCmmcSysLoaderFileId.name: nbsCmmcSysLoaderFileId
nbsCmmcSysLoaderFileId.description: The nbsCmmcSysFirmwareIndex value corresponding to the file being loaded.

nbsCmmcSysLoaderProgress.name: nbsCmmcSysLoaderProgress
nbsCmmcSysLoaderProgress.description: Percentage of file transferred so far.

nbsCmmcSysLoaderStatus.name: nbsCmmcSysLoaderStatus
nbsCmmcSysLoaderStatus.description: Status of this file transfer. The value idle (1) indicates this loader session is unused. The value transferring (2) indicates this transfer is underway. The value completed (3) indicates this transfer finished successfully. The value aborted (4) indicates the transfer was stopped before completion.

nbsCmmcSysLoaderAbort.name: nbsCmmcSysLoaderAbort
nbsCmmcSysLoaderAbort.description: This object allows users to prematurely halt this loader session. If this loader session can not be aborted, the agent will report notSupported(1). If nbsCmmcSysLoaderStatus is transferring(2) and this feature is supported, the agent will report supported(2). When a GET on this object returns supported(2), a user may set this object to abort(3). Doing so will cause the agent to stop the transfer and change nbsCmmcSysLoaderStatus to aborted(4). The agent should report the values of nbsCmmcSysLoaderFileId and nbsCmmcSysLoaderProgress as the state they were in at the time of the abort. Please note that aborting a loader session will leave the destination memory bank with a corrupted, unusable firmware image. It is important for users to correct this promptly, by (re)transferring a good and complete firmware image.

nbsCmmcSysLoaderAck.name: nbsCmmcSysLoaderAck
nbsCmmcSysLoaderAck.description: This object allows users to ACKnowledge the termination of this loader session. If nbsCmmcSysLoaderStatus is idle(1) or transferring(2), the agent will report this object as notSupported(1). If nbsCmmcSysLoaderStatus is completed(3) or aborted(4), the agent should report supported(2). When a GET on this object returns supported(2), a user may set this object to acknowledge(3). Doing so will cause the agent to either: - delete this entire row of the nbsCmmcSysLoaderTable, or - reset this row to its idle state by clearing both nbsCmmcSysLoaderFileId and nbsCmmcSysLoaderProgress to zero, and changing nbsCmmcSysLoaderStatus to idle(1).

nbsCmmcSysLoaderFilename.name: nbsCmmcSysLoaderFilename
nbsCmmcSysLoaderFilename.description: A copy of nbsCmmcSysFirmwareFilename, for display.

nbsCmmcSysFirmwareURL.name: nbsCmmcSysFirmwareURL
nbsCmmcSysFirmwareURL.description: Remote URL in the form: scheme://[username[:password]@]IP[:port][/path/]filename to use for the remote entry in FirmwareTable. When set, the remote URL will be retrieved and checked for compatability. If it is a valid firmware file, a row in FirmwareTable will be instantiated to represent this file. The corresponding FirmwareFilename will be set to the URL, and FirmwareType set accordingly. The file may or not be cached locally if this row is chosen for a Chassis or SlotFirmwareLoad. If the user has changed the remote file after FirmwareURL is set, but before a Chassis or SlotFirmwareLoad is initiated, the results are undefined. If the remote file has changed, setting this object again will 'refresh' its FirmwareTable entry. If a zero length string is set, the corresponding FirmwareType in the FirmwareTable row will be changed to 'deleted', and any local cache of the file deleted. If an invalid URL is set, or the remote file is invalid or does not exist, the corresponding FirmwareTable row will be changed to 'deleted'. If port is omitted, an appropriate port according to the scheme will be automatically selected Note that only numeric IPs are supported; there is no resolver. If a remote file fetch is in progress, or any Chassis or SlotFirmwareLoad involving a remote URL is in progress, sets to this object will be rejected. This object is not stored in the running configuration. It is an 'impulse' object.

nbsCmmcSysFirmwareURLStatus.name: nbsCmmcSysFirmwareURLStatus
nbsCmmcSysFirmwareURLStatus.description: The state of the URL fetch process initiated by a write to SysFirmwareURL. Setting the Chassis or SlotFirmwareLoad object to the URL index will be rejected unless this object returns completed(4).

nbsCmmcSysNVAreaTableSize.name: nbsCmmcSysNVAreaTableSize
nbsCmmcSysNVAreaTableSize.description: The number of non-volatile firmware flash image areas system wide

nbsCmmcSysNVAreaTable.name: nbsCmmcSysNVAreaTable
nbsCmmcSysNVAreaTable.description: Table that lists firmware images loaded on a chassis, slot, or port.

nbsCmmcSysNVAreaIfIndex.name: nbsCmmcSysNVAreaIfIndex
nbsCmmcSysNVAreaIfIndex.description: Interface index in the form CCSSPPP

nbsCmmcSysNVAreaBank.name: nbsCmmcSysNVAreaBank
nbsCmmcSysNVAreaBank.description: Number of this memory bank / storage area. Numbering must start from one, and bank numbers must be contiguous.

nbsCmmcSysNVAreaStatus.name: nbsCmmcSysNVAreaStatus
nbsCmmcSysNVAreaStatus.description: invalid(1) indicates this entry is not a valid NV area. primary(2) indicates this entry is the primary NV area. The next time the hardware is reset, this image will be loaded. This setting may be changed via nbsCmmcChassisNVAreaAdmin or nbsCmmcSlotNVAreaAdmin. backup(3) indicates this entry is the backup NV area. The next time the hardware is reset, this image will be loaded if the primary image fails to load. This image is subject to being overwritten if a new image is downloaded and there are no other banks available. erased(4) indicates this entry refers to an area that was erased and is no longer in the NV storage area. busy(5) indicates this NV area is busy.

nbsCmmcSysNVAreaVersion.name: nbsCmmcSysNVAreaVersion
nbsCmmcSysNVAreaVersion.description: The version of the firmware package

nbsCmmcSysNVAreaCksum.name: nbsCmmcSysNVAreaCksum
nbsCmmcSysNVAreaCksum.description: The checksum of the metadata. Used to uniquely identify this NV area. Invalid NV areas have a zero Cksum. Not supported value: 0

nbsCmmcPrvIpAddr.name: nbsCmmcPrvIpAddr
nbsCmmcPrvIpAddr.description: The SNMP Agent Administrative value of the IP Address for the private in-band access. This value is stored in the system NVRAM. The current operational IP Address may be obtained by accessing the ipAdEntAddr entry in the ipAddrTable, for ipAdEntIfIndex equal to the private interface value. If the system has no current operational IP Address, meaning that, the access is done out-of-band, then this value takes effect immediately. In this case the NetMask and the BcastAddr will be automatically built. Otherwise it will take effect after a system reset.

nbsCmmcPrvNetMask.name: nbsCmmcPrvNetMask
nbsCmmcPrvNetMask.description: The SNMP Agent Administrative value of the subnet mask for the private in-band access. This value is stored in the system NVRAM. The current operational IP Adress may be obtained by accessing the ipAdEntNetMask entry in the ipAddrTable, for ipAdEntIfIndex equal to the private interface value. If the system has no current operational IP Address, meaning that the access is done out-of-band, then this value takes effect immediately. Otherwise it will take effect after a system reset

nbsCmmcPrvBcastAddr.name: nbsCmmcPrvBcastAddr
nbsCmmcPrvBcastAddr.description: The SNMP Agent Administrative value of the IP Broad- cast Address for the private in-band access. This value is stored in the system NVRAM. The current operational IP Adress may be obtained via the ipAdEntBcastAddr entry in the ipAddrTable for ipAdEntIfIndex equal to the private interface value. If the system has no current operational IP Address, meaning that the access is done out-of-band, then this value takes effect immediately. Otherwise it will take effect after a system reset

nbsCmmcSysIpAddr.name: nbsCmmcSysIpAddr
nbsCmmcSysIpAddr.description: The SNMP Agent Administrative value of the IP Address for the system. This value is stored in the system NVRAM. The current operational IP Adress may be obtained by accessing the ipAdEntAddr entry in the ipAddrTable for ipAdEntIfIndex equal to the system interface value. If the system has no current operational IP Address, meaning that the access is done out-of-band, then this value takes effect immediately. In this case the NetMask and the BcastAddr will be automatically built. Otherwise it will take effect after a system reset.

nbsCmmcSysNetMask.name: nbsCmmcSysNetMask
nbsCmmcSysNetMask.description: The SNMP Agent Administrative value of the subnet mask for the system. This value is stored in the system NVRAM. The current operational IP Adress may be obtained by accessing the ipAdEntNetMask entry in the ipAddrTable for ipAdEntIfIndex equal to the system interface value If the system has no current operational IP Address, meaning that the access is done out-of-band, then this value takes effect immediately. Otherwise it will take effect after a system reset

nbsCmmcSysBcastAddr.name: nbsCmmcSysBcastAddr
nbsCmmcSysBcastAddr.description: The SNMP Agent Administrative value of the IP Broadcast Address for the system. This value is stored in the system NVRAM. The current operational IP Adress may be obtained by accessing the ipAdEntBcastAddr entry in the ipAddrTable for ipAdEntIfIndex equal to the system interface value. If the system has no current operational IP Address, meaning that the access is done out-of-band, then this value takes effect immediately. Otherwise it will take effect after a system reset

nbsCmmcSysObIpAddr.name: nbsCmmcSysObIpAddr
nbsCmmcSysObIpAddr.description: The SNMP Agent Administrative value of the IP Address for the out-band access. This value is stored in the system NVRAM. The current operational IP Adress may be obtained by accessing the ipAdEntAddr entry in the ipAddrTable, for ipAdEntIfIndex equal to the SLIP interface value. If the system has no current operational Out-Band IP Address, meaning that, the access is done in-band, then this value takes effect immediately. In this case the NetMask and the BcastAddr will be automa- tically built. Otherwise it will take effect after a system reset

nbsCmmcSysObNetMask.name: nbsCmmcSysObNetMask
nbsCmmcSysObNetMask.description: The SNMP Agent Administrative value of the subnet mask for the out-band access. This value is stored in the system NVRAM. The current operational IP Adress may be obtained by accessing the ipAdEntNetMask entry in the ipAddrTable, for ipAdEntIfIndex equal to the SLIP interface value. If the system has no current operational Out-Band IP Address, meaning that, the access is done in-band, then this value takes effect immediately. Otherwise it will take effect after a system reset

nbsCmmcSysObBcastAddr.name: nbsCmmcSysObBcastAddr
nbsCmmcSysObBcastAddr.description: The SNMP Agent Administrative value of the IP Broadcast Address for the in-band access. This value is stored in the system NVRAM. The current operational IP Adress may be obtained by accessing the ipAdEntBcastAddr entry in the ipAddrTable, for ipAdEntIfIndex equal to the SLIP interface value. If the system has no current operational Out-Band IP Address, meaning that, the access is done in-band, then this value takes effect immediately. Otherwise it will take effect after a system reset

nbsCmmcSysDefaultGateway.name: nbsCmmcSysDefaultGateway
nbsCmmcSysDefaultGateway.description: The SNMP Agent Administrative value of the Default Gateway. This value is stored in the system NVRAM. The current operational Default Gateway IP Adress may be obtained by accessing ipRouteNextHop object of the 0.0.0.0 entry in the ipRouteTable. If the system has no current operational Default Gateway IP Address, then this value takes effect immediately. Otherwise it will take effect after a system reset.

nbsCmmcSysAdminBootpState.name: nbsCmmcSysAdminBootpState
nbsCmmcSysAdminBootpState.description: This object indicates whether the NM should automatically retrieve its IP settings from its local network using BootP or DHCP. This setting will be stored in persistent memory, and thus preserved over system resets and power cycles.

nbsCmmcSysRunBootpState.name: nbsCmmcSysRunBootpState
nbsCmmcSysRunBootpState.description: This object indicates whether BootP or DHCP was enabled when the NM last booted.

nbsCmmcSysSerialLineMode.name: nbsCmmcSysSerialLineMode
nbsCmmcSysSerialLineMode.description: The mode in which the serial line is used: by the local Administrative Interface, or as a SLIP line. Note that setting this object to adminIf(1) value while in SLIP mode will abort the serial connection between the SNMP Manager and the device. Setting this object to slipIf(2) while in Administrative Interface Mode will abort the local terminal connection.

nbsCmmcSysSerialSlipBaudRate.name: nbsCmmcSysSerialSlipBaudRate
nbsCmmcSysSerialSlipBaudRate.description: The Serial Line Baud Rate when in SLIP Mode. This value is stored in the system NVRAM as well as in the SNMP Agent current configuration.

nbsCmmcSysArpAgingTime.name: nbsCmmcSysArpAgingTime
nbsCmmcSysArpAgingTime.description: The aging time for the ARP table.

nbsCmmcSysMaxTelnetSessions.name: nbsCmmcSysMaxTelnetSessions
nbsCmmcSysMaxTelnetSessions.description: The maximum number of entries in nbsCmmcSysTelnetTable.

nbsCmmcSysTelnetTable.name: nbsCmmcSysTelnetTable
nbsCmmcSysTelnetTable.description: A table describing the Telnet Sessions

nbsCmmcSysTelnetEntry.name: nbsCmmcSysTelnetEntry
nbsCmmcSysTelnetEntry.description: Contains the information describing a Telnet Session

nbsCmmcSysTelnetSessionIndex.name: nbsCmmcSysTelnetSessionIndex
nbsCmmcSysTelnetSessionIndex.description: The index in the Telnet Table for this entry.

nbsCmmcSysTelnetSessionStat.name: nbsCmmcSysTelnetSessionStat
nbsCmmcSysTelnetSessionStat.description: This object indicates if there is any TELNET session in progress.

nbsCmmcSysTelnetHost.name: nbsCmmcSysTelnetHost
nbsCmmcSysTelnetHost.description: This object indicates the remote IP host that connected to the local device. It is 0.0.0.0 if there is no active Telnet session

nbsCmmcSysTelnetHostPort.name: nbsCmmcSysTelnetHostPort
nbsCmmcSysTelnetHostPort.description: This object indicates the port number of the remote IP host.

nbsCmmcSysTelnetLocal.name: nbsCmmcSysTelnetLocal
nbsCmmcSysTelnetLocal.description: This object indicates the IP address of the local device. It is 0.0.0.0 if there is no active Telnet session

nbsCmmcSysTelnetLocalPort.name: nbsCmmcSysTelnetLocalPort
nbsCmmcSysTelnetLocalPort.description: This object indicates the local port number.

nbsCmmcSysTelnetSessionId.name: nbsCmmcSysTelnetSessionId
nbsCmmcSysTelnetSessionId.description: The internal session identifier for this entry.

nbsCmmcSysTelnetConnectTime.name: nbsCmmcSysTelnetConnectTime
nbsCmmcSysTelnetConnectTime.description: This object indicates the length of time connected.

nbsCmmcSysTelnetHostAddressType.name: nbsCmmcSysTelnetHostAddressType
nbsCmmcSysTelnetHostAddressType.description: This object indicates the remote host address type.

nbsCmmcSysTelnetHostAddress.name: nbsCmmcSysTelnetHostAddress
nbsCmmcSysTelnetHostAddress.description: This object indicates the remote host address, IPv4 or IPv6. This field supercedes nbsCmmcSysTelnetHost

nbsCmmcSysTelnetLocalAddressType.name: nbsCmmcSysTelnetLocalAddressType
nbsCmmcSysTelnetLocalAddressType.description: This object indicates the local host address type.

nbsCmmcSysTelnetLocalAddress.name: nbsCmmcSysTelnetLocalAddress
nbsCmmcSysTelnetLocalAddress.description: This object indicates the local host address, IPv4 or IPv6. This field supercedes nbsCmmcSysTelnetLocal

nbsCmmcSysMaxPingSessions.name: nbsCmmcSysMaxPingSessions
nbsCmmcSysMaxPingSessions.description: The maximum number of Ping Sessions allowed in this system.

nbsCmmcSysPingTable.name: nbsCmmcSysPingTable
nbsCmmcSysPingTable.description: A table describing the Ping Sessions

nbsCmmcSysPingEntry.name: nbsCmmcSysPingEntry
nbsCmmcSysPingEntry.description: Contains the information describing a Ping Session

nbsCmmcSysPingSessionIndex.name: nbsCmmcSysPingSessionIndex
nbsCmmcSysPingSessionIndex.description: Index in the Ping Session Table.

nbsCmmcSysPingSessionStat.name: nbsCmmcSysPingSessionStat
nbsCmmcSysPingSessionStat.description: This object controls the activity of the PING process progress. If GET idlePing(1) shows that the ping process is idle If SET idlePing(1) stops an active ping process, if any. If GET runPing(2) shows an active ping process. If SET runPing(2) starts an active ping process, if none active. This has to be the last SET in order to activate the PING process

nbsCmmcSysPingAddr.name: nbsCmmcSysPingAddr
nbsCmmcSysPingAddr.description: The IP Address to which the NM device will ping. Setting this variable initiates the ping sequence. The default value is the loopback address 127.0.0.1.

nbsCmmcSysPingNumber.name: nbsCmmcSysPingNumber
nbsCmmcSysPingNumber.description: The number of ICMP echo packets (pings) to be sent. The default value is 1.

nbsCmmcSysPingOwner.name: nbsCmmcSysPingOwner
nbsCmmcSysPingOwner.description: If a Ping Process is active, then the value of this object shows who activated it: the Administrative Interface, the SNMP Agent or a Web Based Manager.

nbsCmmcSysPingRequests.name: nbsCmmcSysPingRequests
nbsCmmcSysPingRequests.description: The number of ICMP echo request (pings) sent.

nbsCmmcSysPingResponses.name: nbsCmmcSysPingResponses
nbsCmmcSysPingResponses.description: The number of ICMP echo response packets received.

nbsCmmcSysPingAddressType.name: nbsCmmcSysPingAddressType
nbsCmmcSysPingAddressType.description: The IP Address to which the NM device will ping. Setting this variable initiates the ping sequence. The default value is the loopback address 127.0.0.1.

nbsCmmcSysPingAddress.name: nbsCmmcSysPingAddress
nbsCmmcSysPingAddress.description: The IP Address to which the NM device will ping. Setting this variable initiates the ping sequence. The default value is the loopback address 127.0.0.1. Supercedes the field nbsCmmcSysPingAddr

nbsCmmcSysTelnetServer.name: nbsCmmcSysTelnetServer
nbsCmmcSysTelnetServer.description: The telnet server ships disabled by default on the NM2. Not supported means that the telnet server status cannot be changed from SNMP.

nbsCmmcSysSshServer.name: nbsCmmcSysSshServer
nbsCmmcSysSshServer.description: The ssh server ships enabled by default on the NM2. Not supported means that the ssh server status cannot be changed from SNMP.

nbsCmmcSysIpAddrOper.name: nbsCmmcSysIpAddrOper
nbsCmmcSysIpAddrOper.description: The IP address actually being used by the Agent. The Agent's IP address may be assigned automatically by a bootp or DHCP server, or a static IP may be assigned via the nbsCmmcSysIpAddr object.

nbsCmmcSysNetMaskOper.name: nbsCmmcSysNetMaskOper
nbsCmmcSysNetMaskOper.description: The subnet mask actually being used by the Agent. The Agent's subnet mask may be assigned automatically by a bootp or DHCP server, or may be assigned via the nbsCmmcSysNetMask object.

nbsCmmcSysBcastAddrOper.name: nbsCmmcSysBcastAddrOper
nbsCmmcSysBcastAddrOper.description: The IP Broadcast address actually being used by the Agent. The Agent's IP Broadcast address may be assigned automatically by a bootp or DHCP server, or may be assigned via the nbsCmmcSysBcastAddr object.

nbsCmmcSysDefaultGatewayOper.name: nbsCmmcSysDefaultGatewayOper
nbsCmmcSysDefaultGatewayOper.description: The Default Gateway actually being used by the Agent. The Agent's Default Gateway may be assigned automatically by a bootp or DHCP server, or may be assigned via the nbsCmmcSysBcastAddr object.

nbsCmmcSysWebServer.name: nbsCmmcSysWebServer
nbsCmmcSysWebServer.description: The web server ships enabled by default on the NM2. Not supported means that the web server status cannot be changed from SNMP.

nbsCmmcSysWebPort.name: nbsCmmcSysWebPort
nbsCmmcSysWebPort.description: The TCP/UDP/IP port the Agent will listen on for web (HTTP) traffic when nbsCmmcSysWebServer is enabled(3). Not supported value: -1

nbsCmmcSysTelnetPort.name: nbsCmmcSysTelnetPort
nbsCmmcSysTelnetPort.description: The TCP/IP port the Agent will listen on for Telnet traffic when nbsCmmcSysTelnetServer is enabled(3). Not supported value: -1

nbsCmmcSysSshPort.name: nbsCmmcSysSshPort
nbsCmmcSysSshPort.description: The TCP/UDP/IP port the Agent will listen on for Secure Shell (SSH) traffic if nbsCmmcSysSshServer is enabled(3). Not supported value: -1

nbsCmmcSysScpServer.name: nbsCmmcSysScpServer
nbsCmmcSysScpServer.description: The Secure Copy Protocol (SCP) server ships disabled by default on the NM2. This feature shares nbsCmmcSysSshPort with SSH, and will not work unless nbsCmmcSysSshServer is enabled(3). Not supported means that the scp server status cannot be changed from SNMP.

nbsCmmcSysNetconfServer.name: nbsCmmcSysNetconfServer
nbsCmmcSysNetconfServer.description: The Netconf server ships disabled by default. Not supported means that the Netconf server status cannot be changed from SNMP.

nbsCmmcSysNetconfPort.name: nbsCmmcSysNetconfPort
nbsCmmcSysNetconfPort.description: The TCP/UDP/IP port the Agent will listen on for Netconf traffic if nbsCmmcSysNetconfServer is enabled(3). Not supported value: -1

nbsCmmcSysWriteCommunity.name: nbsCmmcSysWriteCommunity
nbsCmmcSysWriteCommunity.description: The SNMP Agent Administrative value of the write community string. This value is stored in the system NVRAM. It will take effect after a system reset. The object may not be read for obvious security reasons. A GET request will be answered by a zero length string.

nbsCmmcSysReadCommunity.name: nbsCmmcSysReadCommunity
nbsCmmcSysReadCommunity.description: The SNMP Agent Administrative value of the read community string. This value is stored in the system NVRAM. It will take effect after a system reset

nbsCmmcSysTrapTblMaxSize.name: nbsCmmcSysTrapTblMaxSize
nbsCmmcSysTrapTblMaxSize.description: The maximum size (number of rows) allowed in the trap table

nbsCmmcSysTrapTable.name: nbsCmmcSysTrapTable
nbsCmmcSysTrapTable.description: A table of managers to whom will the traps generated by the SNMP agent will be sent. It represents the current operational table as well as the NVRAM saved table. The entries in the table are saved over system resets and power up cycles

nbsCmmcSysTrapEntry.name: nbsCmmcSysTrapEntry
nbsCmmcSysTrapEntry.description: Contains the information necessary to generate a trap to be sent to a particular manager. The object nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntStatus, when written is used to create or delete an entry/row in nbsCmmcSysTrapTable. To create a new entry a SET PDU with the nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntRecipient, nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntComm and nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntStatus objects is required.

nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntIndex.name: nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntIndex
nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntIndex.description: The index of the entry/row in the trap table in the range 1 to the value of nbsCmmcSysTrapTblMaxSize.

nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntStatus.name: nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntStatus
nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntStatus.description: This object is used to get/set the validity of the information contained by nbsCmmcSysTrapEntry row. Setting this object to the value invalid(1) has the effect of deleting the corresponding nbsCmmcSysTrapTable entry. Deleting and entry has the effect of initializing it to default values : IpAddr = 0.0.0.0 & Comm = null string. Setting this object to the value valid(2) entry has the effect of creating a new row in the nbsCmmcSysTrapTable object, if an entry with the same nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntIpAddr does not exist. If such an entry exists, then a 'badValue' error will be returned. The GET operations will receive a value of valid(2) for existing entries. An invalid(1) value indicates an entry that was deleted by a previous SET operation.

nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntIpAddr.name: nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntIpAddr
nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntIpAddr.description: IPv4 Address of a manager that is to receive the SNMP agent traps. This field is now read-only and is superseded CmmcSysTrapTblEntRecipient

nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntComm.name: nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntComm
nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntComm.description: Community string used by the SNMP agent in the traps generated to this SNMP manager/receiver.

nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntLevel.name: nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntLevel
nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntLevel.description: Event severity level threshold for this SNMP manager. If the event severity level is at least nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntLevel, the SNMP agent will generate a trap to this SNMP manager/receiver.

nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntPort.name: nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntPort
nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntPort.description: The UDP/IP port on the Manager to which the Agent will send SNMP traps/notifications. Not supported value: -1

nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntAddressType.name: nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntAddressType
nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntAddressType.description: The address type of nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntRecipient. Currently ipv4 and ipv6 are supported.

nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntRecipient.name: nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntRecipient
nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntRecipient.description: IP Address (IPv4 or IPv6) or hostname of a manager that is to receive the SNMP agent generated traps; supersedes nbsCmmcSysTrapTblEntIpAddr

nbsCmmcSysEnablePowerSupplyTraps.name: nbsCmmcSysEnablePowerSupplyTraps
nbsCmmcSysEnablePowerSupplyTraps.description: Indicates whether powerSupplyAllarmOn and powerSupplyAllarmOff traps in this MIB should be generated.

nbsCmmcSysEnableModuleTraps.name: nbsCmmcSysEnableModuleTraps
nbsCmmcSysEnableModuleTraps.description: Indicates whether moduleUp and moduleDown traps in this MIB should be generated.

nbsCmmcSysEnableBridgeTraps.name: nbsCmmcSysEnableBridgeTraps
nbsCmmcSysEnableBridgeTraps.description: Indicates whether newRoot and topologyChange traps in the BRIDGE-MIB should be generated.

nbsCmmcSysEnableIpAccessTraps.name: nbsCmmcSysEnableIpAccessTraps
nbsCmmcSysEnableIpAccessTraps.description: Indicates whether IP access traps in this MIB should be generated.

nbsCmmcSysSnmpPortAdmin.name: nbsCmmcSysSnmpPortAdmin
nbsCmmcSysSnmpPortAdmin.description: The UDP/IP port the Agent will listen on for SNMP traffic after the next system restart. Not supported value: -1

nbsCmmcSysSnmpPortOper.name: nbsCmmcSysSnmpPortOper
nbsCmmcSysSnmpPortOper.description: The UDP/IP port the Agent is listening on for SNMP traffic now. Not supported value: -1

nbsCmmcSysTftpHostIP.name: nbsCmmcSysTftpHostIP
nbsCmmcSysTftpHostIP.description: This is the IP Address of the TFTP Server/Client serving the actual TFTP transfer. A TFTP transfer may mean a software/microcode/parameter/etc.. download/upload process, initiated by the SNMP agent, for one of the modules, including, but not only, the System Control Card. It is 0.0.0.0, if th TFTP host is undefined.

nbsCmmcTftpMaxSessionNum.name: nbsCmmcTftpMaxSessionNum
nbsCmmcTftpMaxSessionNum.description: Maximum number of parallel TFTP sessions that are supported by the system

nbsCmmcTftpSessTable.name: nbsCmmcTftpSessTable
nbsCmmcTftpSessTable.description: A table that describes the active TFTP sessions

nbsCmmcTftpSessEntry.name: nbsCmmcTftpSessEntry
nbsCmmcTftpSessEntry.description: Contains a description of a particular TFTP session

nbsCmmcTftpSessIndex.name: nbsCmmcTftpSessIndex
nbsCmmcTftpSessIndex.description: The index of the TFTP session (1..nbsCmmcTftpMaxSessionNum)

nbsCmmcTftpSessStatus.name: nbsCmmcTftpSessStatus
nbsCmmcTftpSessStatus.description: The status of this TFTP session

nbsCmmcTftpSessHostIp.name: nbsCmmcTftpSessHostIp
nbsCmmcTftpSessHostIp.description: This is the IP Address of the TFTP Host (Server/Client) serving the TFTP session as a source/destination. An IP address of 0.0.0.0 signifies that no setup has been done. Setting the nbsCmmcTftpSessHostIp value will change also the the default of all the instances of nbsCmmcTftpSessHostIp that were not specifically initialized by a SET operation.

nbsCmmcTftpSessModuleId.name: nbsCmmcTftpSessModuleId
nbsCmmcTftpSessModuleId.description: Deprecated. Module Id that owns this TFTP session (whose firmware/microcode/parameters/etc. are transferred

nbsCmmcTftpSessAction.name: nbsCmmcTftpSessAction
nbsCmmcTftpSessAction.description: This object is used to initiate a TFTP file transfer. If nbsCmmcTftpSessStatus is not active (4), the Agent should report the value inactive (1). The Manager may initiate a session between the Agent and the host specified in nbsCmmcTftpSessHostIp by changing the value of this object. Setting the value downloadNM (2) tells the Agent to transfer its firmware image from the host to itself. Setting the value uploadNM (3) tells the Agent to transfer its firmware image from itself to the host. Setting the value downloadPar (4) tells the Agent to transfer a previous backup of its configuration from the host to itself. Setting the value uploadPar (5) tells the Agent to send a backup file of its current configuration to the host. For any other type of file, the Manager should set this value to downloadFile (6) to send a file from the host to the NM, and uploadFile (7) to transfer a file from the NM to the host.

nbsCmmcTftpSessFileName.name: nbsCmmcTftpSessFileName
nbsCmmcTftpSessFileName.description: The name of the file to be transferred by this TFTP session.

nbsCmmcTftpSessFileSize.name: nbsCmmcTftpSessFileSize
nbsCmmcTftpSessFileSize.description: The number of bytes in the file. Whichever side has the file being sent may report the file size here. Not supported value: -1

nbsCmmcTftpSessProgress.name: nbsCmmcTftpSessProgress
nbsCmmcTftpSessProgress.description: The number of bytes successfully transferred in this session. Not supported value: -1

nbsCmmcTftpSessAddressType.name: nbsCmmcTftpSessAddressType
nbsCmmcTftpSessAddressType.description: This is the IP Address Type of the TFTP Host (Server/Client) serving the TFTP session as a source/destination.

nbsCmmcTftpSessAddress.name: nbsCmmcTftpSessAddress
nbsCmmcTftpSessAddress.description: This is the IPv4 or IPv6 Address of the TFTP Host (Server/Client) serving the TFTP session as a source/destination. Setting the nbsCmmcTftpSessAddress value will change also the the default of all the instances of nbsCmmcTftpSessAddress that were not specifically initialized by a SET operation. This supercedes nbsCmmcTftpSessHostIp.

nbsCmmcSysTftpHostAddress.name: nbsCmmcSysTftpHostAddress
nbsCmmcSysTftpHostAddress.description: Supercedes the previous value of nbsCmmcSysTftpHostIP; this is the IP Address of the TFTP Server/Client serving the actual TFTP transfer. A TFTP transfer may mean a software/microcode/parameter/etc.. download/upload process, initiated by the SNMP agent, for one of the modules, including, but not only, the System Control Card. It is unknown, if the TFTP host is undefined.

nbsCmmcChassisTable.name: nbsCmmcChassisTable
nbsCmmcChassisTable.description: A table that describes the Chassis connected

nbsCmmcChassisEntry.name: nbsCmmcChassisEntry
nbsCmmcChassisEntry.description: Contains a description of a particular Chassis

nbsCmmcChassisModel.name: nbsCmmcChassisModel
nbsCmmcChassisModel.description: The model name of the chassis.

nbsCmmcChassisNumberOfSlots.name: nbsCmmcChassisNumberOfSlots
nbsCmmcChassisNumberOfSlots.description: The number of slots in the Chassis.

nbsCmmcChassisHardwareRevision.name: nbsCmmcChassisHardwareRevision
nbsCmmcChassisHardwareRevision.description: The hardware revision of the chassis.

nbsCmmcChassisTemperature.name: nbsCmmcChassisTemperature
nbsCmmcChassisTemperature.description: The temperature (degrees Celsius) of the Chassis. Not supported value: 0x80000000

nbsCmmcChassisTemperatureLimit.name: nbsCmmcChassisTemperatureLimit
nbsCmmcChassisTemperatureLimit.description: The maximum safe temperature (degrees Celsius) of the Chassis. Not supported value: 0x80000000

nbsCmmcChassisTemperatureMin.name: nbsCmmcChassisTemperatureMin
nbsCmmcChassisTemperatureMin.description: The minimum safe temperature (degrees Celsius) of the Chassis. Not supported value: 0x80000000

nbsCmmcChassisSignalStrengthMinimum.name: nbsCmmcChassisSignalStrengthMinimum
nbsCmmcChassisSignalStrengthMinimum.description: The minimum recommended operational received signal strength.

nbsCmmcChassisEnableAutoReset.name: nbsCmmcChassisEnableAutoReset
nbsCmmcChassisEnableAutoReset.description: Continuously monitor slots for module changes, and reset if new board installed. Deprecated. The response to any GET should be notSupported(1). Any SET attempt should be rejected with the SNMP error badValue(3).

nbsCmmcChassisEnableLinkTraps.name: nbsCmmcChassisEnableLinkTraps
nbsCmmcChassisEnableLinkTraps.description: When set, send trap to report change in link status, up or down.

nbsCmmcChassisEnableChassisTraps.name: nbsCmmcChassisEnableChassisTraps
nbsCmmcChassisEnableChassisTraps.description: When set, send trap to report chassis related events.

nbsCmmcChassisEnableLoopbackTraps.name: nbsCmmcChassisEnableLoopbackTraps
nbsCmmcChassisEnableLoopbackTraps.description: When set, send trap to report change in loopback configuration.

nbsCmmcChassisEnableSlotChangeTraps.name: nbsCmmcChassisEnableSlotChangeTraps
nbsCmmcChassisEnableSlotChangeTraps.description: When set, send trap to report slot change related events.

nbsCmmcChassisEnablePortTraps.name: nbsCmmcChassisEnablePortTraps
nbsCmmcChassisEnablePortTraps.description: When set, send trap to report port change related events.

nbsCmmcChassisResetAllModules.name: nbsCmmcChassisResetAllModules
nbsCmmcChassisResetAllModules.description: Continuously monitor slots for module changes, and reset if new board installed. Deprecated. The response to any GET should be notSupported(1). Any SET attempt should be rejected with the SNMP error badValue(3).

nbsCmmcChassisEnableModuleSpecificTraps.name: nbsCmmcChassisEnableModuleSpecificTraps
nbsCmmcChassisEnableModuleSpecificTraps.description: When set, send trap to report change in specific cards conditions

nbsCmmcChassisLoopbackTimeout.name: nbsCmmcChassisLoopbackTimeout
nbsCmmcChassisLoopbackTimeout.description: loopback timeout in minutes, zero indicates forever

nbsCmmcChassisName.name: nbsCmmcChassisName
nbsCmmcChassisName.description: The user assigned name for this chassis

nbsCmmcChassisEnableLINTraps.name: nbsCmmcChassisEnableLINTraps
nbsCmmcChassisEnableLINTraps.description: When off(2), suppresses any traps related to Link Integrity Notification.

nbsCmmcChassisEnablePortChangeTraps.name: nbsCmmcChassisEnablePortChangeTraps
nbsCmmcChassisEnablePortChangeTraps.description: When off(2), suppresses any traps related to removable Ports being inserted or removed.

nbsCmmcChassisEnablePortDiagsTraps.name: nbsCmmcChassisEnablePortDiagsTraps
nbsCmmcChassisEnablePortDiagsTraps.description: When off(2), suppresses any traps related to digital diagnostics being outside of safe levels.

nbsCmmcChassisEnableSwitchoverTraps.name: nbsCmmcChassisEnableSwitchoverTraps
nbsCmmcChassisEnableSwitchoverTraps.description: When on, NM can send notifications whenever a self-healing card switches traffic from an active port to its redundant standby port. When off, NM will not send switchover notifications.

nbsCmmcChassisCrossConnect.name: nbsCmmcChassisCrossConnect
nbsCmmcChassisCrossConnect.description: For chassis housing cross-connect blades or slots, this object is used to reflect the operating state and to clear the entire cross-connect map, including any independent maps of subordinate slots. If there are currently no cross-connect blades or slots in this chassis, the Agent must report notSupported(1). Additionally, if this object reports notSupported(1), any SNMP SET to this object should return SNMP Error 3 (bad value). The Agent should report operating(2) under normal circumstances. If this object reports operating(2), SNMP Managers are allowed to set this object to clearing (3), which instructs the Agent to erase all this chassis' cross-connect maps, including any independent maps of subordinate slots.

nbsCmmcChassisNVAreaBanks.name: nbsCmmcChassisNVAreaBanks
nbsCmmcChassisNVAreaBanks.description: The maximum number of executable images that can be stored locally on this chassis. This number does not count any memory banks that are in a modular subcomponent of this chassis. Please refer to nbsPartProgNVAreaStart and nbsPartProgNVAreaBanks for that information. Not supported value: 0

nbsCmmcChassisFirmwareCaps.name: nbsCmmcChassisFirmwareCaps
nbsCmmcChassisFirmwareCaps.description: This bitmask indicates which executable images this chassis can support. This object is mandatory for all chassis. Bit 0 is reserved. Subsequent bits refer to the nbsCmmcSysFirmwareTable. Bit 1 corresponds to the first table entry, Bit 2 to the second entry, and so on. A bit is set (1) if that image is appropriate for this chassis, cleared (0) otherwise. OCTET STRING bitmasks count the leftmost bit (MSB) as 0. A zero length OCTET STRING indicates that the nbsCmmcSysFirmwareTable is not supported by this agent.

nbsCmmcChassisFirmwareLoad.name: nbsCmmcChassisFirmwareLoad
nbsCmmcChassisFirmwareLoad.description: This bitmask indicates which executable images this chassis has stored in its own NV area. This object is mandatory for all chassis. OCTET STRING bitmasks count the leftmost bit (MSB) as 0. Bit 0 indicates whether an executable image is loading. Subsequent bits refer to the nbsCmmcSysFirmwareTable. Bit 1 corresponds to the first table entry, Bit 2 to the second entry, and so on. A bit is set (1) if that image is stored on this chassis, cleared (0) if not. Clearing bits has no effect. To erase an NV area, use the nbsCmmcSysNVAreaTable. Users may transfer a file to an NV area by setting the appropriate file's bit and the loading (MSB) bit to one (1). Adding a file requires that the NM start a file transfer to this chassis, which is a lengthy operation. If a transfer session is already active (nbsCmmcChassisLoader is non-zero), writes to this object will be rejected. A zero length OCTET STRING indicates that the nbsCmmcSysFirmwareTable is not supported by this agent.

nbsCmmcChassisNVAreaAdmin.name: nbsCmmcChassisNVAreaAdmin
nbsCmmcChassisNVAreaAdmin.description: A SET on this object will force the corresponding nbsCmmcSysNvAreaStatus to primary, set this chassis' other memory banks to backup, and immediately load and execute the firmware image contained in the specified memory bank. A GET on this object will indicate the memory bank of this chassis that is currently designated as primary. Not supported value: -1

nbsCmmcChassisNVAreaOper.name: nbsCmmcChassisNVAreaOper
nbsCmmcChassisNVAreaOper.description: The nbsCmmcSysNVAreaBank of nbsCmmcSysNVAreaTable corresponding to the current operationally active firmware image. 0 indicates the current active image is NOT in the NVAreaTable. Not supported value: -1

nbsCmmcChassisLoader.name: nbsCmmcChassisLoader
nbsCmmcChassisLoader.description: The nbsCmmcSysLoaderIndex of nbsCmmcSysLoaderTable corresponding to the current loading session. 0 indicates no loading session is active.

nbsCmmcChassisSerialNum.name: nbsCmmcChassisSerialNum
nbsCmmcChassisSerialNum.description: SerialNumber of this chassis. If this object is not supported, this string should be empty.

nbsCmmcChassisFace.name: nbsCmmcChassisFace
nbsCmmcChassisFace.description: ASCII string containing encoded summary of chassis front panel status. The encoding uses keywords and associated allowed values. Keyword:value pairs delimited by the pipe '|' symbol, and within a pair, a keyword should be separated from its associated value by a colon ':' character. Agent should provide the following info if available. If unknown, it should be omitted. Description Keyword Allowed Values --------------------------------------------------------- Protocol prot ether|slip Power Supply(X) psx [use nbsCmmcChassisPSxStatus] Temperature temp [use nbsCmmcChassisTemperature] Temperature Max tmax [use nbsCmmcChassisTemperatureLimit] Temperature Min tmin [use nbsCmmcChassisTemperatureMin] Type type [use nbsCmmcChassisType] RM/AH Peer Chas rmch [use nbsCmmcChassisIndex] An example string could be: |prot:ether|ps1:2|ps2:3|ps3:5|temp:20| If this object is not supported, this string should be empty.

nbsCmmcChassisCountersState.name: nbsCmmcChassisCountersState
nbsCmmcChassisCountersState.description: This object allows user to reset MAC counters on all ports in this Chassis.

nbsCmmcChassisPowerStatus.name: nbsCmmcChassisPowerStatus
nbsCmmcChassisPowerStatus.description: Indicates if the total power in the chassis is sufficient or insufficient. Insufficient means that the chassis won't work in a correct mode.

nbsCmmcChassisCount.name: nbsCmmcChassisCount
nbsCmmcChassisCount.description: The number of chassis currently plugged into the system.

nbsCmmcSlotTable.name: nbsCmmcSlotTable
nbsCmmcSlotTable.description: A table that describes the Slot connected

nbsCmmcSlotEntry.name: nbsCmmcSlotEntry
nbsCmmcSlotEntry.description: Contains a description of a particular Slot

nbsCmmcSlotChassisIndex.name: nbsCmmcSlotChassisIndex
nbsCmmcSlotChassisIndex.description: The index of the Chassis to the Slot is connected.

nbsCmmcSlotType.name: nbsCmmcSlotType
nbsCmmcSlotType.description: The front panel of card in the slot.

nbsCmmcSlotModel.name: nbsCmmcSlotModel
nbsCmmcSlotModel.description: Describes the model of card that is currently in the slot.

nbsCmmcSlotObjectId.name: nbsCmmcSlotObjectId
nbsCmmcSlotObjectId.description: The description of the type of card in the slot.

nbsCmmcSlotNumberOfPorts.name: nbsCmmcSlotNumberOfPorts
nbsCmmcSlotNumberOfPorts.description: Number of ports on the card.

nbsCmmcSlotHardwareRevision.name: nbsCmmcSlotHardwareRevision
nbsCmmcSlotHardwareRevision.description: This describes the hardware revision of the card

nbsCmmcSlotReset.name: nbsCmmcSlotReset
nbsCmmcSlotReset.description: Current reset condition, and possible reset types. notSupported [1] - reported if feature unavailable. operating [2] - indicates normal operating status. phy [3] and queue [4] are deprecated. resetSlot [5] - cold restart, may impact traffic. initSlot [6] reverts to default settings; init-module. resetWarm [7] - soft restart, won't hurt traffic. The value operating [2] is normally returned by GET, but during a reset operation, the appropriate reset value [5, 6, or 7] may be returned.

nbsCmmcSlotName.name: nbsCmmcSlotName
nbsCmmcSlotName.description: The user assigned name for this slot.

nbsCmmcSlotModuleType.name: nbsCmmcSlotModuleType
nbsCmmcSlotModuleType.description: Equivalent to nbsCmmcSlotType, except for modules that occupy more than one slot in a chassis. For such multi- slot modules, this ModuleType indicates the product this slot is a part of.

nbsCmmcSlotModuleSlot.name: nbsCmmcSlotModuleSlot
nbsCmmcSlotModuleSlot.description: This indicates the position of this slot within its module. For one-slot modules this value is always one (1). For multi-slot modules, this is a positive integer between 1 and the number of slots spanned by this module. The numbering always begins with the leftmost slot as 1.

nbsCmmcSlotSwConfigurable.name: nbsCmmcSlotSwConfigurable
nbsCmmcSlotSwConfigurable.description: Indicates whether card is software configurable, usually based on hardware jumper/dip switch settings. If any changes to the hardware configuration are allowed, this value will be yes(3). If this is no(2), SNMP GETs will work but SETs will fail with an SNMP error. According to RFC 1157, that error should be noSuchName(2).

nbsCmmcSlotConfiguration.name: nbsCmmcSlotConfiguration
nbsCmmcSlotConfiguration.description: Bit stream containing current configuration of slot.

nbsCmmcSlotMacAddress.name: nbsCmmcSlotMacAddress
nbsCmmcSlotMacAddress.description: MAC Address of this card. If this object is not supported, this string should be empty.

nbsCmmcSlotIPAddress.name: nbsCmmcSlotIPAddress
nbsCmmcSlotIPAddress.description: For non-NM cards which feature independent IP stacks, this is the SNMP Agent Administrative value of the IP Address for the card in this slot.

nbsCmmcSlotSubnetMask.name: nbsCmmcSlotSubnetMask
nbsCmmcSlotSubnetMask.description: For non-NM cards which feature independent IP stacks, this is the SNMP Agent Administrative value of the SubnetMask for the card in this slot.

nbsCmmcSlotBroadcastAddr.name: nbsCmmcSlotBroadcastAddr
nbsCmmcSlotBroadcastAddr.description: For non-NM cards which feature independent IP stacks, this is the SNMP Agent Administrative value of the IP Broadcast Address for the card in this slot.

nbsCmmcSlotDefGateway.name: nbsCmmcSlotDefGateway
nbsCmmcSlotDefGateway.description: For non-NM cards which feature independent IP stacks, this is the SNMP Agent Administrative value of the Default Gateway for the card in this slot.

nbsCmmcSlotHoming.name: nbsCmmcSlotHoming
nbsCmmcSlotHoming.description: This object describes the cabling topology of CO / CPE pairs. It must be supported on the Customer Premises Equipment (CPE) slots. Any card that does not utilize this object should report notSupported(1). If one CO is redundantly cabled to one CPE, the pair is in singleCO(2) homing. If two separate CO cards are connected to the same CPE, the CPE is dually homed. Because neither CO has contact with the other CO, each CO should be told the CPE is in a dualCOs(3) homing configuration. If the card has a dual homing feature but does not know its current status, it defaults to singleCO(2). If that is incorrect, users should change the value to dualCOs(3) to inform the card of its network configuration.

nbsCmmcSlotRedundancyAdmin.name: nbsCmmcSlotRedundancyAdmin
nbsCmmcSlotRedundancyAdmin.description: This object is used to disable redundancy on certain cards that support the 802.3ah standard, but if supported, the preferred method is to use the object nbsCmmcPortEnableAdmin to administratively disable redundant ports that shouldn't become active. This object may also be used to change the operating mode of 4 port crossbar cards that can be configured for redundancy. For cards that do not support this feature, any reads of this object should get the response notSupported (1). Writes to this object should be rejected with the SNMP error badValue (3).

nbsCmmcSlotUpgradable.name: nbsCmmcSlotUpgradable
nbsCmmcSlotUpgradable.description: This object indicates whether the card in this slot can now be reprogrammed. It should be used together with nbsCmmcSysUpgrade. Cards without reprogrammable firmware should always report notSupported (1). Reprogrammable cards should report supported(2) only if the NM has the appropriate firmware image already loaded and ready to send to the card.

nbsCmmcSlotCrossConnect.name: nbsCmmcSlotCrossConnect
nbsCmmcSlotCrossConnect.description: For slots supporting cross-connect functionality, this object is used to reflect the operating state and clear the entire cross-connect map for this slot. If the slot is not of cross-connect type, the Agent must report notSupported(1). Additionally, if this object reports notSupported(1), any SNMP SET to this object should return SNMP Error 3 (bad value). The Agent should report operating(2) under normal circumstances. If this object reports operating(2), SNMP Managers are allowed to set this object to clearing (3), which instructs the Agent to erase the cross-connect map for this slot.

nbsCmmcSlotClearType.name: nbsCmmcSlotClearType
nbsCmmcSlotClearType.description: When nbsCmmcSysLockTypes is enabled, use this object to clear the configured slot type. Issue a set command with a value of clearType(3). A read of this object will always return idle(2), or notSupported(1) if this feature is not supported.

nbsCmmcSlotNVAreaBanks.name: nbsCmmcSlotNVAreaBanks
nbsCmmcSlotNVAreaBanks.description: The maximum number of executable images that can be stored locally on this module. This number does not count any memory banks that are in a modular subcomponent of this card. Please refer to nbsPartProgNVAreaStart and nbsPartProgNVAreaBanks for that information. Not supported value: 0

nbsCmmcSlotFirmwareCaps.name: nbsCmmcSlotFirmwareCaps
nbsCmmcSlotFirmwareCaps.description: This bitmask indicates which executable images this module can support. This object is mandatory for all modules. Bit 0 is reserved. Subsequent bits refer to the nbsCmmcSysFirmwareTable. Bit 1 corresponds to the first table entry, Bit 2 to the second entry, and so on. A bit is set (1) if that image is appropriate for this module, cleared (0) if unavailable. OCTET STRING bitmasks count the leftmost bit (MSB) as 0. A zero length OCTET STRING indicates that the nbsCmmcSysFirmwareTable is not supported by this agent.

nbsCmmcSlotFirmwareLoad.name: nbsCmmcSlotFirmwareLoad
nbsCmmcSlotFirmwareLoad.description: This bitmask indicates which executable images this module has stored in its own NV area. This object is mandatory for all modules. OCTET STRING bitmasks count the leftmost bit (MSB) as 0. Bit 0 indicates whether an executable image is loading. Subsequent bits refer to the nbsCmmcSysFirmwareTable. Bit 1 corresponds to the first table entry, Bit 2 to the second entry, and so on. A bit is set (1) if that image is stored on this module, cleared (0) if not. Clearing bits has no effect. To erase an NV area, use the nbsCmmcSysNVAreaTable. Users may transfer a file to an NV area by setting the appropriate file's bit and the loading (MSB) bit to one (1). Adding a file requires that the NM start a file transfer to this module, which is a lengthy operation. If a transfer session is already active (nbsCmmcSlotLoader is non-zero), writes to this object will be rejected. A zero length OCTET STRING indicates that the nbsCmmcSysFirmwareTable is not supported by this agent.

nbsCmmcSlotNVAreaAdmin.name: nbsCmmcSlotNVAreaAdmin
nbsCmmcSlotNVAreaAdmin.description: A SET on this object will force the corresponding nbsCmmcSysNvAreaStatus to primary, set this module's other memory banks to backup, and immediately load and execute the firmware image contained in the specified memory bank. A GET on this object will indicate the memory bank of this module that is currently designated as primary. Not supported value: -1

nbsCmmcSlotNVAreaOper.name: nbsCmmcSlotNVAreaOper
nbsCmmcSlotNVAreaOper.description: The nbsCmmcSysNVAreaBank of nbsCmmcSysNVAreaTable corresponding to the current operationally active firmware image. 0 indicates the current active image is NOT in the NVAreaTable. Not supported value: -1

nbsCmmcSlotLoader.name: nbsCmmcSlotLoader
nbsCmmcSlotLoader.description: The nbsCmmcSysLoaderIndex of nbsCmmcSysLoaderTable corresponding to the current loading session. 0 indicates no loading session is active.

nbsCmmcSlotSerialNum.name: nbsCmmcSlotSerialNum
nbsCmmcSlotSerialNum.description: SerialNumber of this module. If this object is not supported, this string should be empty.

nbsCmmcSlotToggleRate.name: nbsCmmcSlotToggleRate
nbsCmmcSlotToggleRate.description: For crossbar products. Used to indicate the approximate rate, in microseconds, at which this card should toggle its transmitters on and off. Not supported value: 0

nbsCmmcSlotTemperature.name: nbsCmmcSlotTemperature
nbsCmmcSlotTemperature.description: The temperature (in degrees celsius) of this slot. Not supported value: 0x80000000

nbsCmmcSlotCountersState.name: nbsCmmcSlotCountersState
nbsCmmcSlotCountersState.description: This object allows user to reset MAC counters on all ports.

nbsCmmcSlotRedundancyOper.name: nbsCmmcSlotRedundancyOper
nbsCmmcSlotRedundancyOper.description: This object reports the actual redundancy state of a card. For cards that do not support this feature, any reads of this object should get the response notSupported (1).

nbsCmmcSlotModuleStatus.name: nbsCmmcSlotModuleStatus
nbsCmmcSlotModuleStatus.description: Slots that have no card installed should be reported as empty(2). Slots where a card has been physically inserted should be reported as notReady(3) while the card is loading or warming up, and ready(4) once the card is fully operational. Slots that support redundant action may report standby(5) if they are not yet ready but waiting to go to ready(4) in case of failover. When this object is unavailable the Agent will report the status notSupported (1).

nbsCmmcLedTable.name: nbsCmmcLedTable
nbsCmmcLedTable.description: A table to report status of front panel LEDs

nbsCmmcLedEntry.name: nbsCmmcLedEntry
nbsCmmcLedEntry.description: Indicates status of a particular LED

nbsCmmcLedChassisIndex.name: nbsCmmcLedChassisIndex
nbsCmmcLedChassisIndex.description: The index of the Chassis to the Slot is connected.

nbsCmmcLedIndex.name: nbsCmmcLedIndex
nbsCmmcLedIndex.description: The index of the led. Index starts at 1.

nbsCmmcLedDescription.name: nbsCmmcLedDescription
nbsCmmcLedDescription.description: LED's label as on card and short description

nbsCmmcSlotFaceTable.name: nbsCmmcSlotFaceTable
nbsCmmcSlotFaceTable.description: A table that describes the front panel state of each slot

nbsCmmcSlotFaceEntry.name: nbsCmmcSlotFaceEntry
nbsCmmcSlotFaceEntry.description: Contains a description of a particular Slot

nbsCmmcSlotFaceChassisIndex.name: nbsCmmcSlotFaceChassisIndex
nbsCmmcSlotFaceChassisIndex.description: The index of the Chassis housing this slot.

nbsCmmcSlotFaceSummary.name: nbsCmmcSlotFaceSummary
nbsCmmcSlotFaceSummary.description: ASCII string containing encoded summary of slot front panel status. The encoding uses keywords and associated allowed values. Keyword:value pairs delimited by the pipe '|' symbol, and within a pair, a keyword should be separated from its associated value by a colon ':' character. Agent should provide the following info if available. If unknown or inapplicable, it should be omitted. Description Keyword Allowed Values --------------------------------------------------------- Slot/SNMP Type slid [use nbsCmmcSlotType] LED ledx [use nbsCmmcLedColor] PortLink plnkx [use nbsCmmcPortLinked] PortOperational popx [use nbsCmmcPortOperational] PortSelectLink pselx actv|stdby PortConnector pconx [use nbsCmmcPortConnector] An example string could be: |slid:436|led1:2|plnk1:2|pop2:2|psel2:actv|pcon4:15| If this object is not supported, this string should be empty.

nbsCmmcPortTable.name: nbsCmmcPortTable
nbsCmmcPortTable.description: A table that describes the Port connected

nbsCmmcPortEntry.name: nbsCmmcPortEntry
nbsCmmcPortEntry.description: Contains a description of a particular Port.

nbsCmmcPortChassisIndex.name: nbsCmmcPortChassisIndex
nbsCmmcPortChassisIndex.description: The index of the Chassis for the Slot to which this port is connected.

nbsCmmcPortSlotIndex.name: nbsCmmcPortSlotIndex
nbsCmmcPortSlotIndex.description: The index of the Slot in the Chassis to which this port is connected.

nbsCmmcPortIndex.name: nbsCmmcPortIndex
nbsCmmcPortIndex.description: The index of the Port in the Slot in the Chassis to which this port is connected.

nbsCmmcPortType.name: nbsCmmcPortType
nbsCmmcPortType.description: The physical type of port. Valid port types are > 1. The mib representation of pluggable port types are documented in nbsSffMsaIdentifier from NBS-SFF-MIB, and have the following PortTypes here: sfp 125, gbic 147, xfp 197, qsfp 219, cxp 220, cfp 221, qspf28 223, cfp2 224

nbsCmmcPortLink.name: nbsCmmcPortLink
nbsCmmcPortLink.description: The link status of the port.

nbsCmmcPortAutoNegotiation.name: nbsCmmcPortAutoNegotiation
nbsCmmcPortAutoNegotiation.description: The AutoNegotiation status of a port. AutoNegotiation may affect the port's speed, duplex, and MDI/MDIX. If this port does not offer this feature, Agent should report the value notSupported(1). To disable this feature, set the value to off(2). To enable this feature, set the value to on(3). The value autoMDIXOnly(4) is deprecated. The value custom (5) is deprecated.

nbsCmmcPortDuplex.name: nbsCmmcPortDuplex
nbsCmmcPortDuplex.description: The duplex mode of the port.

nbsCmmcPortSpeed.name: nbsCmmcPortSpeed
nbsCmmcPortSpeed.description: The line speed of the port. This object is superseded by nbsCmmcPortProtoAdmin and nbsCmmcPortProtoOper.

nbsCmmcPortRxActivity.name: nbsCmmcPortRxActivity
nbsCmmcPortRxActivity.description: The receive status of the port.

nbsCmmcPortTxActivity.name: nbsCmmcPortTxActivity
nbsCmmcPortTxActivity.description: The transmit status of the port.

nbsCmmcPortCollisionActivity.name: nbsCmmcPortCollisionActivity
nbsCmmcPortCollisionActivity.description: The collision status of the port.

nbsCmmcPortLoopback.name: nbsCmmcPortLoopback
nbsCmmcPortLoopback.description: The loopback status of the port.

nbsCmmcPortEnableAdmin.name: nbsCmmcPortEnableAdmin
nbsCmmcPortEnableAdmin.description: Administratively desired operational status of the port. For the actual operational status, please see the related object nbsCmmcPortEnableOper. The value notSupported (1) indicates that the user has no ability to disable the transceiver. Users may set this value to disable (2) to turn off the port's transceiver so that no traffic will flow through this port. For traffic to be sent and received as normal, this object should be set to enable (3). The value auto (4) has been deprecated - older Agents might report it, and Managers may attempt to set it, but newer agents will neither report nor accept this value.

nbsCmmcPortSelectLink.name: nbsCmmcPortSelectLink
nbsCmmcPortSelectLink.description: For ports in self-healing redundant groups, this object describes this port's redundant state. The value notSupported(1) indicates this object is unused for this port. The value standby(2) indicates that traffic is not currently routed through this port. The value active(3) indicates that this port is the selected channel for passing data traffic. This object may be used to choose which port in a redundant group is active. That selection may be overridden by the system as appropriate, such as the link going down, or a preferred port coming up. The values (4) through (6) are deprecated. They will no longer be reported by the Agent, and attempts to set them should be rejected with the SNMP error badValue(3).

nbsCmmcPortLIN.name: nbsCmmcPortLIN
nbsCmmcPortLIN.description: Line integrity check on or off.

nbsCmmcPortRemoteLoopback.name: nbsCmmcPortRemoteLoopback
nbsCmmcPortRemoteLoopback.description: Indicates whether port should perform Remote Loopback. When on (3), outbound traffic is returned to the ingress port. In other words, traffic comes from one of the module's other ports to get to this one, and upon arriving here gets sent back to that other port, from where it continues on back to the originator of the traffic. The related object nbsCmmcPortLoopback may be forced off(2) whenever this object is set to on(3).

nbsCmmcPortErrorActivity.name: nbsCmmcPortErrorActivity
nbsCmmcPortErrorActivity.description: The error activity of the port.

nbsCmmcPortName.name: nbsCmmcPortName
nbsCmmcPortName.description: The user assigned name for this port. This object is also used for the MIB2 object ifAlias.

nbsCmmcPortValue.name: nbsCmmcPortValue
nbsCmmcPortValue.description: Originally named nbsCmmcPortOpticalPower. Now usage may vary by card. For card 162, PortValue measures the Optical Power, or signal strength. For card 197, PortValue is a text string displaying signal strength in decibels. For cards 211 and 212, PortValue measures the current bandwidth level. Only one byte is used, and its value can be notSupported(1), under45Mbps(2), under155Mbps(3), under622Mbps(4), or under1Gbps(5)

nbsCmmcPortThreshold.name: nbsCmmcPortThreshold
nbsCmmcPortThreshold.description: Port Threshold - usage may be different for each card. For card 197, this indicates the minimum signal strength. Value ranges from -5 to -40 decibels. For card 211, valid values are: notSupported(1), speed45Mbps(2), speed155Mbps(3), speed622Mbps(4), speed1Gbps(5) For card 375, this indicates the rate limit and is expressed in units of Mbps. For cards 376 and 379, this indicates the rate limit and is expressed in units of Kbps. Not supported value: 0x80000000

nbsCmmcPortThresholdAction.name: nbsCmmcPortThresholdAction
nbsCmmcPortThresholdAction.description: Action to perform if threshold is crossed. Usage may be different for each card. For card 197, the allowable Actions are: notSupported(1), noAction(2), sendTrap(3) For cards 211 and 212, valid values are: notSupported(1), noAction(2), sendTrap(3), disablePort(4), disablePortAndSendTrap(5),disablePortPeriodically(6), disablePeriodicallyAndSendTrap(7) Not supported value: 1

nbsCmmcPortRMChassis.name: nbsCmmcPortRMChassis
nbsCmmcPortRMChassis.description: The nbsCmmcPortRMChassis, nbsCmmcPortRMSlot, and nbsCmmcPortRMPort objects indicate which remote port is externally cabled to this port. This nbsCmmcPortRMChassis object indicates the remote port's nbsCmmcPortChassisIndex. If no remote port is known, the nbsCmmcPortRMChassis, nbsCmmcPortRMSlot, and nbsCmmcPortRMPort objects should each have the value 0. If a physical link is discovered by the agent, the nbsCmmcPortRMChassis, nbsCmmcPortRMSlot, and nbsCmmcPortRMPort objects are each set automatically. If the connection is not discovered automatically, users may enter the connection by manually setting the three nbsCmmcPortRM objects

nbsCmmcPortRMSlot.name: nbsCmmcPortRMSlot
nbsCmmcPortRMSlot.description: The nbsCmmcPortRMChassis, nbsCmmcPortRMSlot, and nbsCmmcPortRMPort objects indicate which remote port is externally cabled to this port. This nbsCmmcPortRMSlot object indicates the remote port's nbsCmmcPortSlotIndex. If no remote port is known, the nbsCmmcPortRMChassis, nbsCmmcPortRMSlot, and nbsCmmcPortRMPort objects should each have the value 0. If a physical link is discovered by the agent, the nbsCmmcPortRMChassis, nbsCmmcPortRMSlot, and nbsCmmcPortRMPort objects are each set automatically. If the connection is not discovered automatically, users may enter the connection by manually setting the three nbsCmmcPortRM objects

nbsCmmcPortRMPort.name: nbsCmmcPortRMPort
nbsCmmcPortRMPort.description: The nbsCmmcPortRMChassis, nbsCmmcPortRMSlot, and nbsCmmcPortRMPort objects indicate which remote port is externally cabled to this port. This nbsCmmcPortRMPort object indicates the remote port's nbsCmmcPortIndex. If no remote port is known, the nbsCmmcPortRMChassis, nbsCmmcPortRMSlot, and nbsCmmcPortRMPort objects should each have the value 0. If a physical link is discovered by the agent, the nbsCmmcPortRMChassis, nbsCmmcPortRMSlot, and nbsCmmcPortRMPort objects are each set automatically. If the connection is not discovered automatically, users may enter the connection by manually setting the three nbsCmmcPortRM objects

nbsCmmcPortSerialNumber.name: nbsCmmcPortSerialNumber
nbsCmmcPortSerialNumber.description: Part Serial Number as reported by the component. Not supported value: 'N/A'

nbsCmmcPortVendorInfo.name: nbsCmmcPortVendorInfo
nbsCmmcPortVendorInfo.description: Vendor name as reported by the component. Not supported value: 'N/A'

nbsCmmcPortTemperature.name: nbsCmmcPortTemperature
nbsCmmcPortTemperature.description: The temperature (in degrees celsius) of this trans- ceiver. Not supported value: 0x80000000

nbsCmmcPortTxPower.name: nbsCmmcPortTxPower
nbsCmmcPortTxPower.description: The output power (in milli dBm) of this transmitter. Not supported value: 0x80000000

nbsCmmcPortRxPower.name: nbsCmmcPortRxPower
nbsCmmcPortRxPower.description: The received optical power (in milli dBm) of this receiver. Not supported value: 0x80000000

nbsCmmcPortBiasAmps.name: nbsCmmcPortBiasAmps
nbsCmmcPortBiasAmps.description: The bias current (in microAmps) of this transmitter. The reserved value -1 indicates that this object is not supported.

nbsCmmcPortSupplyVolts.name: nbsCmmcPortSupplyVolts
nbsCmmcPortSupplyVolts.description: The supply voltage (in milliVolts) of this transmitter. The reserved value -1 indicates that this object is not supported.

nbsCmmcPortMedium.name: nbsCmmcPortMedium
nbsCmmcPortMedium.description: The type of physical communications medium.

nbsCmmcPortConnector.name: nbsCmmcPortConnector
nbsCmmcPortConnector.description: The type of physical connector or jack.

nbsCmmcPortWavelength.name: nbsCmmcPortWavelength
